      "writtenOn": "2021-12-08T20:28:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i agree that leaving it blank isn\u0027t great.  my qualms is that using \"true\" as a sentinel is also a bit confusing, and doesn\u0027t map well to all possible options.  sometimes we add flags to explicitly disable things.  although minijail\u0027s current set of long options doesn\u0027t encompass it, this is a common pattern we\u0027ve used in CrOS.\n\nconsider minijail\u0027s -N option which enters a new cgroups namespace.  if we made a long option, it might be like --namespace-cgroups.  and if we added a flag to disable it, it\u0027d be --no-namespace-cgroups.  so in the config file, would we write:\n\n no-namespace-cgroups \u003d true\n namespace-cgroups \u003d false\n\nwhat about options that take an argument and we happen to pass \"true\" as the string ?  from reading the config, it\u0027s hard to differentiate them.\n\nconsidering the file syntax, i don\u0027t have a better recommendation than just leaving the value empty.  if we made the \u003d optional, then that might be a good signal ...",
